Subject: RedLevel Advisory #23 - SalesCart Shopping Cart SQL Injection
 Vulnerability

SalesCart Shopping Cart - SQL Injection Vulnerability

SalesCart does not sanitize any forms in cgi-bin/reorder2.asp, allowing an attacker to inject arbitrary SQL queries, as well as possible command execution.

Google d0rk: "Sorry, you have no Items in your Shopping Cart !" inurl:cgi-bin/view1.asp
Vulnerable Variable: All forms in reorder2.asp
Vulnerable File: cgi-bin/reorder2.asp (password: x' OR 'x'='x)
Vendor Status: Notified multiple times, no response. Possible silent patch.

John Martinelli
